President Biden spoke with Prime Minister Suga of Japan at the G7 to discuss various challenges, including COVID-19, climate change, North Korea, China, and peace across the Taiwan Strait. Biden expressed support for strengthening the alliance between the US and Japan, extending cooperation to new areas like the Build Back Better World initiative, and strengthening ties with other allies. He also expressed support for the Tokyo Olympic Games, emphasizing the importance of public health measures to protect athletes and spectators. Biden expressed pride in US athletes participating in the games.